line.comment: * We do not reset inventory here. If we send another team to a previous expedition, we assume they manage to pick up what the other team left behind them.
* Idle mesures how long, in seconds, a marine has to stay in one room before moving to the next one (if nothing happens).
* Enemy distance is how far an enemy is from the squad when entering a new room.
* All the following are per room (same for $min/maxEnemies):
* The base chance the squad has to get spotted when entering a new room. Final chance = $chanceBaseSpotted - $fighting / 4 - $initiative / 10 (minimum 1). $fighting being the average of all marines.
